    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p><hi rend="underline">$40 Enclosed</hi>.</p>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>202 St. Paul Street</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Montreal</placeName>
                <date>Aug. 24th/54</date>
            </p>
            <p><addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee>    <placeName>Phila.</placeName></p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Dear Sir.</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">I returned<lb/> from <placeName>New York</placeName> on
                    <date>Monday</date> and<lb/> found your note of <date>3d</date> inst. with<lb/>
                an enclosed for <persName>Mr. De Sola</persName>, which<lb/> was delivered. Accept
                my heart-<lb/>felt thanks for your kindness.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I leave another favour to ask of<lb/> you, which I am confident you
                will<lb/> kindly execute for me. While<lb/> a Prisoner at
                    <placeName>Wilmington</placeName> I had<lb/> occasion to borrow some money<lb/>
                on a <hi rend="underline">diamond ring</hi> from a <persName><hi rend="underline"
                        >Mr</hi>.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="underline">Raw</hi></persName>, who keeps a clothing store<lb/> in
                    <placeName>Wilmington</placeName> on <placeName>Market Street near<lb/> 4<hi
                        rend="sup">th</hi></placeName>. He loaned me $20, for which<lb/> I promised
                to pay him $23. He<lb/> gave me a receipt for the ring, which<lb/> I forwarded to
                    <persName>Mr. Frankel</persName>. <persName>Mr. F.</persName><lb/> has promised
                to get me the ring, ac-<lb/>cording to the enclosed letter. I also<lb/> owe
                    <persName>Mr. Frankel</persName> $15 which he kind-<lb/>ly loaned me. I
                therefore enclose</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>you $40. in order that you may<lb/> pay <persName>Mr. Frankel</persName> $15 and give<lb/>
                <persName>Mr. F.</persName> $23 to get the ring and $20<lb/> for expense to
                    <placeName>Wilmington</placeName> &amp; return,<lb/> and pay Express on ring to
                        <placeName><hi rend="underline">N. York</hi></placeName></p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">The ring is a single stone <hi rend="underline">pure first</hi><lb/>
                <hi rend="underline">water diamond</hi> ladies ring, chased<lb/> gold.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Please send the ring to <placeName><hi rend="underline">New
                        York</hi></placeName><lb/> by Express addressed to me, and<lb/> marked “to
                be called for”. <hi rend="underline">Please</hi><lb/>
                <hi rend="underline">advise me of having sent it</hi> by <hi rend="underline"
                    >ad</hi>-<lb/><hi rend="underline">dressing</hi> me to <placeName><hi
                        rend="underline">Earles Hotel N. Y.</hi></placeName><lb/> where I shall be
                by <date>Monday</date> next.<lb/> I hope you will be able to forward<lb/> it by that
                time as my wife will<lb/> be waiting for it.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">With great respect and esteem</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Yours Most Gratefully</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">
                <hi rend="underline">
                    <persName role="author">C. M. De La Mar</persName>
                </hi>
            </p>
            <p><persName>Mr. Frankel</persName> or his partner has the order for the<lb/> ring.
                Write me to <placeName>Earles Hotel N.Y.</placeName><lb/> and mark letter “<hi
                    rend="underline">To be called for</hi>”</p>
        </body>
